      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "0ee3487737bd876e233213ccec4e6fca4690093e",
            "subject": "LU-6780 ptlrpc: Do not resend req with allow_replay"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-05-23 14:38:02.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-07-04 01:34:23.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-6380 scrub: handle update_log during initial scrub",
        "message": "LU-6380 scrub: handle update_log during initial scrub\n\nThe normal OI scrub will not run until recovery finished. But the\nupdate logs (update_log, and sub-items under update_log_dir) will\nbe accessed during the recovery. So if the the OI mapping for the\nupdate log cannot be handled before the recovery, then the normal\nOI scrub cannot be started/resumed. To resolve above dependency,\nthe initial OI scrub (that will be triggered by the mount process\nwith sync mode before the recovery) will handle the update logs'\nOI mappings in advance.\n\nIn DNE2, each MDT will have a special FID for update log, during\nrecovery, the failover MDT can retrieve update logs on remote MDT\nby this FID, that said the FID is special and it also has to be\nlocated globally (not local FID). So the MDT index is packed into\nthe FID (as f_oid), then FLD can locate the special FID. To handle\nsuch special FIDs, OI scrub needs to know the target index.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Iac71c20c1f1631efbe19a03e380822cead6c00d1\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/15192\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: wangdi <di.wang@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
  "requirements": [],
  "submit_records": []
